"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-us-swimmers-unnerved-by-latest-chinese-doping-case-ahead-of-paris-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"As the world abruptly shut down due to the COVID-19 pandemic in the spring of 2020, concerns of a canceled Tokyo Olympics were assuaged when it was announced that the Summer Games would be pushed back to 2021.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 43, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.999999994256541, \"rank\": 5.743858165646452e-09, \"text\": \"COVID-19 pandemic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3, \"to\": 12}, {\"ngram\": \"the spring\", \"from\": 64, \"to\": 74}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 92}, {\"ngram\": \"a canceled Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 121}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Games\", \"from\": 163, \"to\": 179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that one-year delay gave rise to new fears within the United States swimming community: doping.\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 309, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 268, \"end\": 281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999593746914, \"rank\": 3.938686625733016e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that one-year delay\", \"from\": 214, \"to\": 233}, {\"ngram\": \"rise\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 243}, {\"ngram\": \"new fears\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With drug testers unable to regularly circulate to do their jobs during that time, there was an opportunity for athletes to use performance-enhancing drugs with a vastly diminished chance of being caught.\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 515, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"drug testers\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 328}, {\"ngram\": \"their jobs\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 375}, {\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 392}, {\"ngram\": \"an opportunity\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 418}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 431}, {\"ngram\": \"performance-enhancing drugs\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 466}, {\"ngram\": \"a vastly diminished chance\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the nation that several U.S. coaches and officials were most concerned about was China, sources told Sports Illustrated at the time.\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999992542346315, \"rank\": 7.457319049569568e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.119002297260779e-52, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the nation\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"several U.S. coaches\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 556}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 570}, {\"ngram\": \"sources\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 615}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 651}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis greatly increases their chances of doping,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d one source said in March 2020.\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"their chances\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 693}, {\"ngram\": \"doping\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"one source\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Roughly six months later, the World Anti-Doping Association\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the global PED watchdog group\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094received what sources labeled an \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cofficial intelligence report\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d with a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cspecific and credible tip\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d about elite-level Chinese swimmers doping.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 813, \"end\": 816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Performance-enhancing_substance\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2693344697151741e-89, \"text\": \"PED\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Performance-enhancing_substance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Performance-enhancing_substance\"}, {\"begin\": 959, \"end\": 966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999926673604561, \"rank\": 7.324914100014984e-06, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"what sources\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 855}, {\"ngram\": \"an \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cofficial intelligence\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cspecific and credible tip\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 940}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The whistleblower named individual swimmers in the intelligence report, sources say.\\u00c2 And about four months after that, the tipster\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s called shot came in: 23 of the country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s swimmers tested positive for Trimetazidine (or TMZ), a banned drug, during a meet in early January 2021.\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 1268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1193, \"end\": 1206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trimetazidine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Trimetazidine\", \"types\": [\"Q8386\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trimetazidine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trimetazidine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the intelligence report\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"sources\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1069}, {\"ngram\": \"the tipster\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s called shot\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1162}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"a banned drug\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1229}, {\"ngram\": \"a meet\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"early January\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1261}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among those who reportedly tested positive were some of the athletes mentioned by name by the whistleblower.\\u00c2 Nothing ever happened to the swimmers who tested positive\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009413 of whom went on to compete for China in the Tokyo Games, with four of those 13 winning medals.\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999992542346315, \"rank\": 7.457319049569568e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1337}, {\"ngram\": \"name\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1355}, {\"ngram\": \"the whistleblower\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 Nothing\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1386}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"those 13 winning medals\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time, the swimming world had no idea about the positive tests, having been kept completely in the dark by WADA, which deviated from its usual policy of publicly identifying athletes who test positive for prohibited substances.\\u00c2 WADA accepted China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s internal investigative findings that the positive tests were the result of inadvertent environmental contamination that occurred at the hotel where the athletes were staying, citing traces of TMZ that were found in the hotel kitchen.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 2031, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming world\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"no idea\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1606}, {\"ngram\": \"the dark\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1647}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1655}, {\"ngram\": \"its usual policy\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1726}, {\"ngram\": \"prohibited substances\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1770}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 WADA\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"internal investigative findings\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1828}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"inadvertent environmental contamination\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"the hotel\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 1938}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1957}, {\"ngram\": \"traces\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1985}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"the hotel kitchen\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No explanation has been offered for how the TMZ, which is used to treat heart conditions, got into the kitchen.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt seems so egregious,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Natalie Coughlin Hall, who won 12 medals across three Olympics, three of them gold.\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2076, \"end\": 2079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.882298163474077e-49, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}, {\"begin\": 2180, \"end\": 2196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Natalie Coughlin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalie_Coughlin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No explanation\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2046}, {\"ngram\": \"heart conditions\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2120}, {\"ngram\": \"the kitchen\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2150}, {\"ngram\": \"12 medals\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2219}, {\"ngram\": \"three Olympics\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cDuring the height of the lockdown, this is exactly what everyone was worried about.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the height\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2284}, {\"ngram\": \"the lockdown\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2300}, {\"ngram\": \"exactly what\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2322}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just a gut punch when you see something like this.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d The entire affair remained a secret until exposes were published in late April of this year by a German television station andThe New York Times.\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2510, \"end\": 2516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9947333507358251, \"rank\": 0.00489503006361931, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just a gut punch\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2397}, {\"ngram\": \"The entire affair\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"a secret\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2447}, {\"ngram\": \"exposes\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"late April\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2490}, {\"ngram\": \"this year\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2503}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA subsequently defended its decision not to publicize the positive tests, saying that it would have unfairly impugned the swimmers\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 reputations.The drug test revelationscreated a cloud that will hover over swimming at the Paris Olympics next month.\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2812, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2563}, {\"ngram\": \"its decision\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2598}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2634}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 reputations\", \"from\": 2680, \"to\": 2707}, {\"ngram\": \"The drug test\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2721}, {\"ngram\": \"a cloud\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2748}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2800}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTo wonder if the competition is going to be fair when you get to Paris?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says 2016 American gold medalist Maya DiRado Andrews.\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2902, \"end\": 2910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.518235522349139e-17, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00