ans\"}, {\"begin\": 6000, \"end\": 6014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Rice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephanie Rice\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Rice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Rice\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ye\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s freestyle split\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5863}, {\"ngram\": \"58.68 seconds\", \"from\": 5867, \"to\": 5880}, {\"ngram\": \"the final 100 meters\", \"from\": 5886, \"to\": 5906}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous world-record holder\", \"from\": 5955, \"to\": 5987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More notable at the time, Ye\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100 free split was just .03 slower than that of men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gold medalist Ryan Lochte, and Ye actually was faster over the final 50 meters (28.93 to 29.10).\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThat last 100 meters was reminiscent of some old East German swimmers, for people who have been around a while,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009dsaidJohn Leonard, executive director of the World Swimming Coaches Association at the time.\\u00c2 Ye, who also went on to win the 200 IM in London, has never tested positive for a banned drug.She has remained competitive internationally, but has not won another Olympic medal since then.\", \"from\": 6016, \"to\": 6604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6136, \"end\": 6138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanye_West\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.990662052550034e-58, \"text\": \"Ye\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanye_West\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kanye_West\"}, {\"begin\": 6256, \"end\": 6267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999999997726263, \"rank\": 2.267145551896392e-10, \"text\": \"East German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"